{"article_id":"5iocBnS1dc3CcCwE","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Redskins branded merchandise sits on display in a sports store in Sterling , VA , July 13 , 2020 .","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"( Leah Millis/Reuters )","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"I don ' t weep for the team name ,","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"but a little humility is in order","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"regarding claims","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"that the name and anyone","depth":11},{"id":6,"text":"who defends it","depth":11},{"id":7,"text":"are uncontroversially deplorable .","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"Were the Washington Redskins right to ditch their longstanding team name in favor of an as-yet-to-be-revealed substitute ?","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"While the Redskins name has been discussed for the better part of a decade ,","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"the debate is part of the broader question of the current madness","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"for tearing down history of all kinds .","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"Is the wiser approach to resist the woke mob at all points","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"( the Texas Rangers are already in the mob ' s sights , on logic opposite to the objection to Redskins ) ,","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"or is it to seek more reasoned distinctions ?","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"Whichever approach you prefer ,","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"let me offer some perspective and my own proposed replacement .","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"There really is a lot of football history at stake .","depth":5},{"id":18,"text":"The Redskins acquired their team name in 1933 .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"That was their second year of operation , in Boston .","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"They moved to Washington in 1937 .","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"Pro football began with the American Professional Football Association in 1920 , a child of the First World War ;","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"this is its centennial .","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"Its successor , the NFL , was founded in 1922 .","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"Just five other NFL franchises date as far back as 1932 :","depth":13},{"id":25,"text":"The Chicago Bears ,","depth":18},{"id":26,"text":"founded 1920 as the Decatur Staleys ,","depth":18},{"id":27,"text":"moved to Chicago","depth":17},{"id":28,"text":"and became the Bears in 1922 .","depth":16},{"id":29,"text":"The Arizona Cardinals ,","depth":20},{"id":30,"text":"founded in 1920 ,","depth":20},{"id":31,"text":"started in Chicago ,","depth":19},{"id":32,"text":"moved to St. Louis in 1960 and Phoenix in 1988 .","depth":18},{"id":33,"text":"The Green Bay Packers and New York Giants were founded in 1921 and 1925 , respectively , under their current names .","depth":18},{"id":34,"text":"The Detroit Lions ,","depth":20},{"id":35,"text":"founded as the Portsmouth Spartans in 1930 ,","depth":20},{"id":36,"text":"acquired their current city and name in 1934 .","depth":19},{"id":37,"text":"The Steelers and Eagles came into the league in 1933 ,","depth":17},{"id":38,"text":"the Rams in 1937 ;","depth":18},{"id":39,"text":"all the other franchises date to after the Second World War .","depth":18},{"id":40,"text":"So the long continuity of the Redskins name is one of the pillars of the league ' s ties to its earliest days .","depth":14},{"id":41,"text":"As the Redskins , the team has won five championships","depth":14},{"id":42,"text":"( three in the Super Bowl era )","depth":14},{"id":43,"text":"and played in the championship game six other times .","depth":13},{"id":44,"text":"I confess my bias :","depth":13},{"id":45,"text":"I have , as a New York Giants fan , hated the Redskins for 40 years ,","depth":14},{"id":46,"text":"never more so","depth":15},{"id":47,"text":"than when I spent a semester in D.C. in the spring of 1992 in the shadow of the Skins ' dominating 1991-92 Super Bowl season .","depth":15},{"id":48,"text":"But there is no question","depth":14},{"id":49,"text":"that the team name has meant a lot to a lot of people for a long , long time .","depth":14},{"id":50,"text":"That kind of tradition is entitled to some weight .","depth":13},{"id":51,"text":"There was a tendency in the early NFL","depth":13},{"id":52,"text":"to either use the local baseball team ' s name","depth":15},{"id":53,"text":"( e.g. , the Giants )","depth":15},{"id":54,"text":"or a variant on it","depth":15},{"id":55,"text":"( e.g. , Bears vs Cubs ) .","depth":15},{"id":56,"text":"The Redskins started off with the former strategy","depth":14},{"id":57,"text":"( the same name as baseball ' s Boston Braves ,","depth":15},{"id":58,"text":"who left Beantown 20 years later ) ,","depth":15},{"id":59,"text":"then shifted to the latter in 1933 ,","depth":14},{"id":60,"text":"doubtless without much of a thought","depth":15},{"id":61,"text":"for whether the two names were meaningfully different .","depth":15},{"id":62,"text":"Is \" Redskins \" a bad word ?","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"Even today , many schools in Native-American communities use Native-American team names ,","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"so perhaps some judgment is called for .","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"My own gut instinct is that \" Redskins \" is quite different from \" Braves \" ;","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"the former is a racial distinction","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"that sounds like a racial slur","depth":14},{"id":68,"text":"- and has often been used as one .","depth":14},{"id":69,"text":"Braves , by contrast , designates the Native-American warrior with all the martial virtues","depth":15},{"id":70,"text":"that conveys ,","depth":15},{"id":71,"text":"and is no different in that regard than teams","depth":15},{"id":72,"text":"naming themselves Warriors , Vikings , Cavaliers , Knights , Crusaders , Rangers , Patriots , 76ers , or other names","depth":16},{"id":73,"text":"that identify with some particular military or nationalistic tradition .","depth":16},{"id":74,"text":"Nobody would insult a man","depth":15},{"id":75,"text":"- to his face or behind his back -","depth":15},{"id":76,"text":"by calling him a brave .","depth":14},{"id":77,"text":"The history of the word redskin , however is somewhat more complex .","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"It remains much in dispute where , when , and how the term \" redskins \" first began to describe Native Americans ,","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"but it is clear that the term was in use as far back as the final third of the 18th century .","depth":14},{"id":80,"text":"Even the Washington Post ' s effort","depth":17},{"id":81,"text":"to trace the etymology","depth":17},{"id":82,"text":"finds it in use as much by the tribes as by whites .","depth":16},{"id":83,"text":"\" Oklahoma , \" for example , was introduced by a Choctaw missionary in one of the 1866 treaties","depth":17},{"id":84,"text":"establishing the territory ;","depth":17},{"id":85,"text":"the term is generally regarded as combining two Choctaw words ,","depth":18},{"id":86,"text":"\" okla \"","depth":20},{"id":87,"text":"meaning people ,","depth":20},{"id":88,"text":"and \" humma \"","depth":20},{"id":89,"text":"meaning \" red. \"","depth":20},{"id":90,"text":"( There are those","depth":18},{"id":91,"text":"who dispute this , too . )","depth":18},{"id":92,"text":"\" Redskins \" acquired more of the nature of a slur in the second half of the nineteenth century ,","depth":14},{"id":93,"text":"as Americans advanced across the frontier","depth":15},{"id":94,"text":"and came to see Native Americans less as equals and more as obstacles .","depth":15},{"id":95,"text":"Words , of course , have traditions of their own ;","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"while it is important for historians and lawyers to understand the language of the past ,","depth":13},{"id":97,"text":"it is not of much cultural relevance today what a term meant in 1815 ,","depth":14},{"id":98,"text":"if that meaning no longer lives .","depth":14},{"id":99,"text":"The odor of a slur is hard to dispel .","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"If any sports team deserves a name change ,","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"it is the Redskins .","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"But does it actually harm anybody today ,","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"or even offend many people","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"who aren ' t going looking for offense","depth":14},{"id":105,"text":"to take ?","depth":14},{"id":106,"text":"It depends on whom you ask , and how .","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"Widely cited polls","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"conducted in 2004 and 2016","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"found little sentiment among Native Americans","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"for demanding a name change :","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"Nine in 10 Native Americans say","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"they are not offended by the Washington Redskins name ,","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"according to a new Washington Post poll","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"that shows","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"how few ordinary Indians have been persuaded by a national movement to change the football team ' s moniker .","depth":12},{"id":116,"text":"The survey of 504 people across every state and the District reveals","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"that the minds of Native Americans have remained unchanged","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"since a 2004 poll by the Annenberg Public Policy Center found the same result .","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"Responses to The Post ' s questions about the issue were broadly consistent","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"regardless of age , income , education , political party or proximity to reservations .","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"80 percent of the poll ' s respondents said","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"they would not be personally offended","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"if someone called them a \" redskin . \"","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"Issue polling , of course , can be notoriously sensitive to how both the questions and the sample of respondents are derived .","depth":7},{"id":125,"text":"The Post has discussed at length its methodology ,","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"which is fairly standard for a public-opinion poll","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"facing the twin challenges","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"of tracking down Native Americans","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"( a hard-to-poll group ,","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"who are disproportionately unlikely to have landlines )","depth":12},{"id":131,"text":"and of figuring out who defines themselves as Native American .","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"Self-definition by Native heritage includes many people","depth":12},{"id":133,"text":"who are not active in their tribes :","depth":12},{"id":134,"text":"\" Tribal members represented 36 percent of interviews","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"conducted","depth":12},{"id":136,"text":"and accounted for 44 percent of the final weighted sample ,","depth":12},{"id":137,"text":"which matches the Census Bureau ' s data on demographic and geographic characteristics . \"","depth":12},{"id":138,"text":"In February , social-science researchers from UC Berkeley and the University of Michigan published their own survey .","depth":7},{"id":139,"text":"They seem to have gone looking to generate pushback on the Post poll .","depth":8},{"id":140,"text":"As Stephanie Fryberg , one of the authors and a member of the Tulalip Tribes of Washington , described her view :","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"\" We can reach out to fans","depth":10},{"id":142,"text":"to help them to understand","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"that they are contributing to the dehumanization of Native people. \"","depth":11},{"id":144,"text":"Fryberg argues","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"that the Post survey is tainted :","depth":10},{"id":146,"text":"One of the things","depth":16},{"id":147,"text":"that we know in science","depth":16},{"id":148,"text":"is that the questions","depth":17},{"id":149,"text":"you ask before and after","depth":17},{"id":150,"text":"influence the response .","depth":16},{"id":151,"text":"For example ,","depth":15},{"id":152,"text":"if I asked you a really serious question about people","depth":18},{"id":153,"text":"who are dying in your community ,","depth":18},{"id":154,"text":"and then I say ,","depth":18},{"id":155,"text":"\" By the way , are you offended by Native mascots ? \"","depth":18},{"id":156,"text":"you see how you can really influence people .","depth":16},{"id":157,"text":"This is true in general .","depth":13},{"id":158,"text":"But","depth":13},{"id":159,"text":"according to the Post ,","depth":14},{"id":160,"text":"that is not what its poll did .","depth":14},{"id":161,"text":"The \" do you find that name offensive ,","depth":15},{"id":162,"text":"or doesn ' t it bother you ? \"","depth":15},{"id":163,"text":"question was the third question on the survey ,","depth":14},{"id":164,"text":"following only questions of racial self-identification .","depth":13},{"id":165,"text":"The Post was more transparent on its methodology","depth":14},{"id":166,"text":"than is often true of public-opinion polls ,","depth":14},{"id":167,"text":"and it released the questionnaire along with a detailed defense","depth":14},{"id":168,"text":"of how it conducted the poll .","depth":14},{"id":169,"text":"That does not make it definitive","depth":12},{"id":170,"text":"- no one poll result ever is , especially an issue poll -","depth":12},{"id":171,"text":"but Fryberg and her co-authors seem to be straining to come up with reasons","depth":13},{"id":172,"text":"to denigrate the Post poll","depth":13},{"id":173,"text":"rather than just presenting their own survey .","depth":12},{"id":174,"text":"That survey , of \" more than 1,000 self-identified adult Native Americans","depth":13},{"id":175,"text":"representing 50 states and 148 tribes","depth":14},{"id":176,"text":"using the Qualtrics online survey platform , \"","depth":14},{"id":177,"text":"found opinions more divided :","depth":12},{"id":178,"text":"49 % of participants in the UC Berkeley study were found to strongly agree or agree","depth":15},{"id":179,"text":"that the Washington Redskins ' name is offensive ,","depth":15},{"id":180,"text":"while 38 % were not bothered by it .","depth":15},{"id":181,"text":"The remainder were undecided or indifferent .","depth":15},{"id":182,"text":"However , the number of those offended rose for study participants","depth":16},{"id":183,"text":"who were heavily engaged in their native or tribal cultures","depth":16},{"id":184,"text":"( 67 % ) ,","depth":15},{"id":185,"text":"young people","depth":16},{"id":186,"text":"( 60 % )","depth":16},{"id":187,"text":"and people with tribal affiliations such as members of federally recognized tribes","depth":16},{"id":188,"text":"( 52 % ) .","depth":16},{"id":189,"text":"As for ideological standpoints , progressive liberals were more likely to oppose the Redskins ' name ,","depth":14},{"id":190,"text":"compared to their more conservative counterparts . . . .","depth":14},{"id":191,"text":"57 %","depth":15},{"id":192,"text":"who strongly identify with being Native American . . .","depth":15},{"id":193,"text":"were found to be deeply insulted . . .","depth":14},{"id":194,"text":"This looks like a microcosm of America today :","depth":12},{"id":195,"text":"Progressives are more apt to claim offense than others ,","depth":13},{"id":196,"text":"and people","depth":15},{"id":197,"text":"whose racial or ethnic identity is a bigger part of their self-image","depth":15},{"id":198,"text":"are more apt to think in those terms about everything .","depth":14},{"id":199,"text":"The latter is a recurring issue in polling by racial and ethnic group .","depth":12},{"id":200,"text":"Polling of Hispanics , for example , can vary dramatically by levels of self-identification or assimilation .","depth":13},{"id":201,"text":"As the survey authors admit ,","depth":14},{"id":202,"text":"\" Individuals","depth":16},{"id":203,"text":"who are high in racial-ethnic identity centrality","depth":16},{"id":204,"text":"are more likely to both perceive and experience group-based discrimination. \"","depth":15},{"id":205,"text":"If you isolated poll respondents","depth":12},{"id":206,"text":"who \" strongly identify with being white , \"","depth":12},{"id":207,"text":"you ' d similarly get some answers rather different from those","depth":12},{"id":208,"text":"produced by a random sampling of white Americans ,","depth":12},{"id":209,"text":"and probably not in a good way .","depth":10},{"id":210,"text":"The Berkeley survey was conducted entirely online ,","depth":8},{"id":211,"text":"and","depth":11},{"id":212,"text":"if you dig into the study ,","depth":13},{"id":213,"text":"you see","depth":13},{"id":214,"text":"it has its own issues","depth":13},{"id":215,"text":"not mentioned in press accounts .","depth":13},{"id":216,"text":"The authors admit in their paper","depth":15},{"id":217,"text":"that it is \" not a truly representative national sample \"","depth":15},{"id":218,"text":"because it \" fell short","depth":15},{"id":219,"text":"in sampling Native Americans with experience","depth":16},{"id":220,"text":"living on reservations. \"","depth":16},{"id":221,"text":"It excluded respondents","depth":14},{"id":222,"text":"who said","depth":16},{"id":223,"text":"they had Native heritage \"","depth":16},{"id":224,"text":"but did not self-identify as Native American . \"","depth":15},{"id":225,"text":"Startlingly , for a poll about a football team , only 31 percent of the respondents were \" Cisgender men , \"","depth":15},{"id":226,"text":"the other 69 percent being \" Cisgender women ; transgender , nonbinary , and genderqueer people ; \"","depth":15},{"id":227,"text":"the Berkeley survey authors found","depth":15},{"id":228,"text":"that the latter were significantly more opposed to the team name .","depth":15},{"id":229,"text":"The Post sample , by contrast , was 49 percent male .","depth":13},{"id":230,"text":"It also appears that the Berkeley survey ' s respondents skewed younger","depth":14},{"id":231,"text":"( typical for an online survey ) ,","depth":14},{"id":232,"text":"with 47 percent under the age of 35 ;","depth":13},{"id":233,"text":"the Post sample had a higher share of respondents age 50 or older","depth":15},{"id":234,"text":"( 39 percent )","depth":15},{"id":235,"text":"than the Berkeley survey ' s 33 percent","depth":15},{"id":236,"text":"who were aged 45 or older .","depth":15},{"id":237,"text":"Again , the younger respondents were much more opposed .","depth":13},{"id":238,"text":"Neither the Post poll nor the Berkeley survey should be taken as gospel .","depth":10},{"id":239,"text":"But at most , they show far more divided and less emphatic opinions , even among Native Americans ,","depth":11},{"id":240,"text":"than you would expect","depth":12},{"id":241,"text":"if you listened only to the social-justice warrior crowd .","depth":12},{"id":242,"text":"I don ' t weep for the team name ,","depth":4},{"id":243,"text":"because it has always sounded offensive to my ears ,","depth":4},{"id":244,"text":"but a little humility is in order","depth":4},{"id":245,"text":"regarding claims","depth":5},{"id":246,"text":"that the name and anyone","depth":7},{"id":247,"text":"who defends it","depth":7},{"id":248,"text":"are just uncontroversially deplorable .","depth":6},{"id":249,"text":"In any event , the name is dead .","depth":4},{"id":250,"text":"What should be the new name ?","depth":4},{"id":251,"text":"John McCormack suggests the Washington Powhatan .","depth":5},{"id":252,"text":"My own longstanding suggestion is much simpler :","depth":7},{"id":253,"text":"the Washington Pigskins .","depth":8},{"id":254,"text":"They ' d still be \" the Skins. \"","depth":9},{"id":255,"text":"You ' d barely have to change the name of \" Hail to the Redskins. \"","depth":9},{"id":256,"text":"The team has long cherished the secondary nickname \" Hogs. \"","depth":6},{"id":257,"text":"And pigskin is , of course , literally synonymous with football .","depth":5},{"id":258,"text":"If football itself is too offensive ,","depth":6},{"id":259,"text":"the NFL has bigger problems than team names .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":519,"left":501,"right":518,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":501,"left":261,"right":500,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":261,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":500,"left":275,"right":499,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":275,"left":270,"right":274,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":270,"left":267,"right":269,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":267,"left":266,"right":8,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":266,"left":2,"right":265,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":265,"left":3,"right":264,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":264,"left":4,"right":263,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":263,"left":262,"right":7,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":262,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":269,"left":9,"right":268,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":268,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":274,"left":272,"right":273,"relation":"restatement","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":272,"left":271,"right":14,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":271,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":273,"left":15,"right":16,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":499,"left":364,"right":498,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":364,"left":17,"right":363,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":363,"left":277,"right":362,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":277,"left":276,"right":20,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":276,"left":18,"right":19,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":362,"left":278,"right":361,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":278,"left":21,"right":22,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":361,"left":331,"right":360,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":331,"left":316,"right":330,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":316,"left":298,"right":315,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":298,"left":23,"right":297,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":297,"left":294,"right":296,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":294,"left":24,"right":293,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":293,"left":292,"right":40,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":292,"left":281,"right":291,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":281,"left":280,"right":28,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":280,"left":279,"right":27,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":279,"left":25,"right":26,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":291,"left":288,"right":290,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":288,"left":284,"right":287,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":284,"left":283,"right":32,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":283,"left":282,"right":31,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":282,"left":29,"right":30,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":287,"left":33,"right":286,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":286,"left":285,"right":36,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":285,"left":34,"right":35,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":290,"left":37,"right":289,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":289,"left":38,"right":39,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":296,"left":295,"right":43,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":295,"left":41,"right":42,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":315,"left":304,"right":314,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":304,"left":301,"right":303,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":301,"